name: DELIVERY FLIGHT! FIRST EVER Flair Airlines 737-8 MAX Landing at Calgary Airport!
description:
Thank you to RadarBox for supporting this plane spotting video! Find out more about them at https://www.radarbox.com/?referrer=AlexAviation

Back in January, Flair Airlines announced that they had procured 13 Boeing 737 MAXs for an extensive expansion plan.

The first of these 737 MAXs was handed over to the airline today, and flew from Boeing Field to Calgary, making Flair Canada's fourth 737 MAX operator!

In doing so, the airline's also honouring their history a little bit - C-FLEJ was a former Boeing 737-400 registration, which has since been retired from the fleet.

Looking forward to seeing more of these over the next few months! Congratulations to Flair!
